LED Light Bulbs+

Save up to $3 per bulb on LED Light Bulbs
Emitting very little heat and averaging 22 years in lifespan, 
highly-efficient LED bulbs use as little as six watts of energy – 
compared to 40 watts with a traditional incandescent bulb. 
LED bulbs can be expensive, but for a limited time, 
you will receive savings of up to $5 per bulb when you buy LEDs at participating retailers.



Promotional period: now - Dec. 31, 2017, or while funds last.*
Discount only applies to qualified LED bulbs.
Limit 12 bulbs per customer. 
Entergy Arkansas does not warrant or endorse any manufacturer.




CFL Bulbs+

Receive free general-purpose (spiral) CFL Bulbs
Compact fluorescent light bulbs use about 75% less energy than standard incandescent bulbs and last up to 10 times longer – saving you more than $40 in electricity costs over each CFL bulb's lifetime. Look for Entergy Arkansas representatives at community events near you.



Advanced Power Strips+

Save up to $10 on Advanced Power Strips
Did you know that many of your electronic devices still use energy and cost you money, even when turned off?  In fact, 75% of the power used by electronics is in "standby mode." Save money and energy by plugging your PC or TV into an advanced power strip (APS).  APSs offer surge protection and the ability to truly "turn off" electronics when not in use. Because the APS cuts the power draw to other devices completely when you turn off your TV or CPU, you will start to see the savings on your bill as soon as you plug it in. 


Entergy Arkansas customers will receive up to $10 off the purchase of an advanced power strip purchased at participating retail locations or through Entergy's online marketplace.
Promotional period: now - Dec. 31, 2017, or while funds last.*




Clothes Washers+

Get $25 back when you purchase an Energy Star clothes washer
Energy Star certified clothes washers use about 25% less energy and 40% less water than traditional models, so you can save as much as $40 each year during the washer's life.  Energy Star models now come in both front- and top-loading models. Plus Energy Star models have a greater tub capacity so you can wash fewer loads to clean the same amount of laundry. 
And receive $25 cash back when you complete a rebate application form and return with your proof of purchase.  Electric models only; must be paired with an electric dryer.

Promotional period: now - Dec. 31, 2017, or while funds last.*




Pool Pumps+

Get up to $300 back when you purchase an Energy Star certified pool pump for your in-ground pool.
Energy Star certified pool pumps save energy by operating at more than one speed.  
Filtration only requires half the flow rate of running a pool cleaner. 
Conventional pool pumps, with only one speed, are set to run at the higher speeds required to clean the pool, rather than simply providing filtration, at all times.  
Therefore the energy required to run the pump during filtration operation is wasted by running faster than necessary. 
An Energy Star certified pool pump can run at different speeds and be programmed to match the pool operation with its appropriate pool pump speed. 
The energy saved is considerable; reducing pump speed by one-half allows the pump to use just one-eighth as much energy.  
These units not only save over a thousand dollars over their lifetime, they also run quieter, and with a $175 rebate for 2-speed and $300 rebate for multi-speed, the payback period is less than a year. 
Application can be made online, or by returning a completed rebate application form along with proof of purchase.  Must be at least 1 horsepower in size, and be installed in an in-ground pool.



Promotional period: now - Dec. 31, 2017, or while funds last.*
Discount only applies to qualified pool pumps.
Limit 2 pool pump rebates per household.
Entergy Arkansas does not warrant or endorse any manufacturer.



We'll offer discounts on other energy-saving appliances throughout the year. So please check this site regularly, and join our email list to receive periodic updates on promotions and tips for saving energy.
