"They did a real good job; they got in and got out. I think it is a good program." – Judy, Swifton Apartments, Swifton, AR



Multifamily Program
Lower your bill with free products from Entergy. 
From light bulbs to showerheads, the Entergy Arkansas Multifamily Program will install energy-saving products at no cost to owners or tenants.
Energy efficiency upgrades will add value to your property by lowering water and sewer costs, as well as lowering energy costs for tenants. Entergy Arkansas will install these free energy-saving products in eligible multifamily properties. 

What's offered in this program? +

This program is designed to benefit both the property manager/owner and tenants.  The energy efficiency upgrades add value to the property, help lower water and sewer costs, and provide tenants with decreased energy costs. This program also offers both direct installation of cost-effective efficiency measures in tenants' units, as well as common area energy surveys to identify opportunities for future energy-efficient improvements and other Entergy Arkansas energy efficiency programs. Services include:

Direct installation of compact fluorescent bulbs in tenants' residences at no direct cost to the resident.
Direct installation of high-efficiency showerheads if there is electric water heating at no direct cost to the tenant.
Direct installation of high-efficiency kitchen and bath aerators if there is electric water heating at no direct cost to the tenant.
Air conditioning tune-up performed by a certified technician to clean your system and adjust the refrigerant charge.
Common area energy efficiency analysis report mailed to the property manager/owner.




Air Conditioning Tune-Ups +


					    

The air conditioning tune-up helps each home's system to run more efficiently and provides better comfort to residents while lowering energy costs. This is achieved by a certified technician cleaning your system and adjusting refrigerant charge.

For information on participating contractors click here.



 



Compact Fluorescent Light Bulbs +

Most CFLs last 10 times longer and use 75 percent less energy than traditional bulbs. Entergy will install CFLs in fixtures or table lamps in each unit. That means less time changing light bulbs and more time saving money on your Entergy bill.



Energy-Efficient Showerheads +

The showerheads use 40 percent less water than standard showerheads. That means less energy used to heat water for showers. Additionally, these self-cleaning showerheads will not corrode and require zero maintenance. Entergy will replace all eligible showerheads with these showerheads.



Kitchen & Bathroom Faucet Aerators +

Entergy will install energy-efficient faucet aerators in kitchens and bathrooms. Made of long-lasting materials, the aerators use approximately 31 percent less water than a standard faucet. That means less energy* used for water heating. 
*Savings will vary with efficiency of water heating system, temperature of incoming and outgoing water, and the number of occupants in the home. 



Energy Survey +

An Entergy Arkansas-qualified field technician will perform an energy survey of your property's common areas at no cost. This will identify ways to improve your property's energy efficiency. At the end of the survey, the technician will provide you with a summary of recommendations. 


Don't wait to save.

Click here to download the complete Program Manual.
Contact the Entergy Arkansas Multifamily Program by email or phone at 866-627-9177. 



 

































































