Agricultural Energy Solutions
Instant incentives. Long-term savings. 
Entergy rewards its agribusiness customers for installing energy-efficient measures.
The goal of the Entergy Arkansas Agricultural Energy Solutions Program is to produce long-term electricity cost savings for agribusinesses by installing energy efficiency measures and replacing aging, inefficient equipment. 
Eligible businesses have two options for participating in the program.
1. Prescriptive (Lighting) 
This option consists of a series of choices with predetermined incentives for a wide selection of common energy-efficient lighting measures, including:

Compact fluorescent light bulbs.
High-performance linear fluorescent replacements.
Pulse-start metal halide.
Lighting controls, including occupancy sensors.

2. Custom (Energy-efficient Technology)
This option offers incentives for more complex, site-specific and cost-effective opportunities for energy-efficient technologies. Custom projects must be able to show specific and verifiable energy savings and costs. Typical custom measures include:

Low-energy livestock waterers.
Exhaust fans.
Circulation fans.
High-volume, low-speed fans.
Milk pre-cooler.
Variable speed controllers for vacuum pumps.
Variable frequency drives.


Program Incentives & Savings+

The program provides financial incentives and technical assistance to help agribusinesses replace aging, inefficient equipment and systems with new, energy-efficient technologies.  
Prescriptive rebate offering
Provides a simple method to make efficient choices by offering predetermined incentives for a wide selection of common energy-efficient lighting measures, such as compact fluorescent bulbs.
Custom rebate offering
Incentives for more complex and site-specific opportunities for energy-efficient technologies or multi-measure projects that are not included in the prescriptive offerings. Typical custom measures include exhaust fans, variable frequency drives, new construction lighting and circulation fans.  




How does my business benefit from this program? +

An energy-efficient facility not only means a lower energy bill for your business, but also improved employee comfort and productivity. By providing incentives and assistance to agribusinesses that are replacing inefficient equipment, Entergy helps reduce up-front improvement costs, as well as long-term energy bills. Plus, Entergy allows customers to engage their own qualified contractors or in-house staff for improvements.



Who is eligible? +

The Entergy Arkansas Agricultural Energy Solutions Program is available to all non-residential electric customers on the following agriculture rate schedules:

Agricultural pumping.
General farm service.
Small general service.
Large general service.

This program extends to a variety of agribusiness, including poultry, dairy, cattle, swine, Delta/row crops and aquaculture facilities.


Start Saving Today.

Click here to download the complete Program Manual.
Learn more about the Agricultural Energy Solutions Program and how it can benefit your business. Contact program account manager Cody Allen by email or by telephone at 501-244-9570 to get started today!
Please note: An applicant considered a "Free Rider" will be disqualified from program participation. A "Free Rider" is someone who would install an energy efficiency measure without any program incentives or intervention.



 

































































